st resources? Checkstyle doesn't scan resources, so maybe it’s okay to use CC0? \\n\\nExisting Java sources have headers, but should I add one for the resource Java files? If they're source files, perhaps the GWT compiler won’t mind comments. It might not be necessary, but I want to ensure I'm conforming properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating compile issue**\\n\\nI’m noticing that the `renderer.render(builder)` call could create a potential issue with the compilation process. It seems like it might require generated renderer implementation methods and also need to compile the generated code. So, it’s good that I’m spotting this now, as it could lead to some complications if I don’t address it early on! I want to stay on top of this and make sure everything goes smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented dedicated coverage for `com.google.gwt.uibinder.rebind.UiBinderWriter`.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/src/test/java/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/UiBinderWriterTest.java`\n  - Runs the GWT compiler against a small UiBinder/UiRenderer module.\n  - Exercises parser lookup/instantiation and UiRenderer event dispatch generation.\n  - Catches Native Image unsupported dynamic class-loading `Error`s via `NativeImageSupport`.\n\n- GWT test module/resources under:\n  - `tests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/src/test/resources/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/uibinder/`\n  - Includes:\n    - `UiBinderWriterCoverage.gwt.xml`\n    - `client/UiBinderWriterEntryPoint.java`\n    - `client/ClickRenderer.java`\n    - `client/ClickTarget.java`\n    - `client/ClickRenderer.ui.xml`\n\nThis should drive execution through the remaining `UiBinderWriter` dynamic-access sites for:\n\n- `findEventTypeName`\n- `getParserForClass`\n- `getParsersForClass`\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per your instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09de418f8f07b97f0169f5611df7ac819d8415bbd913771e11\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": 